Hung Hsiu-chu, former chairperson of the Chinese Kuomintang (KMT) party arrived in Beijing on Wednesday, a Chinese mainland spokesperson said Thursday. She will attend the opening ceremony of the Beijing 2022 Olympic Winter Games on Friday at invitation, said Ma Xiaoguang, spokesperson for the Taiwan Affairs Office of the State Council. (With input from Xinhua) (Cover: Hung Hsiu-chu, former KMT chairperson, speaks to reporters in Fuzhou City, east China's Fujian Province, July 18, 2021. /CFP)